The paper deals with the coordination of multiple agents, which is a key topic in the field of multi-agent systems (MAS). Therefore, cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the design of controllers for the agents, which falls under the scope of cs.RO (Robotics). The presence of stochastic uncertainties and the need for robustness suggest that the paper may also be relevant to cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper uses analytical proofs and simulation results to demonstrate the efficacy of the proposed solution, which aligns with the scope of cs.LG (Machine Learning).
